sentences: That same year, his cousin took him to see Babatunde Olatunji and his "Drums of Passion", and Olatunji's influence was so great that Michael took on his first name.

His first album as leader, Levels of Consciousness was released in 1979.
He did not release another, Level of Intent, until 1996, putting it on his own label, Diaspora Records.
He mortgaged his home to get the album released, but it was not widely distributed until Motéma reissued it in 2003.
In 2010, Babatunde and Virginia moved to Pennsylvania to teach at Gettysburg College.
